{"parentUuid":"7168d75f-f500-4bee-a3db-10d93dd255ee","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a4e4c9b00c5efe637","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccvuiqh3bgJCQCYTNYPQg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both deliverables are written and the self-audit passed. Summary of what I produced and the key decisions.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- `/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/plan.md` — full layered plan + STRIDE threat model + ASVS block + Mermaid DFD + copy-paste visualization prompt.\n- `/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/acceptance.md` — 14 traceable criteria (`criteria_total: 14`, `delegated_criteria: []`).\n- **No `tasks.md`** — the honest estimate is **7 files (< 8)**, below the F-M4′-1 decomposition threshold, so this builds single-shot.\n\n## How it fits the existing surface (studied, not invented)\n\nThe endpoint aggregates the pre-computed **`usage_rollup`** table — `SUM(event_count) GROUP BY metric` over the day's 24 UTC hour-buckets — which is the same \"read the rollup, not the events\" discipline `GET /v1/usage` (`src/services/usage_service.py`) already follows, keeping per-request cost bounded. It reuses `scoped_transaction` + the `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS policy (migration 0002), the `require_api_key` + Tier-2 throttle sibling-dependency composition, and the central error envelope. It's delivered as a **new sibling module trio** (schema/service/route) + one additive repo function + one `include_router` line, so every existing endpoint's code path is byte-for-byte untouched (the no-behavior-change constraint is diff-auditable).\n\n## Load-bearing decisions surfaced for the checkpoint\n\n1. **400-not-422 for `date`** — the brief pins 400, but the codebase's Pydantic query models return 422. Resolved by binding `date` as an optional `str` on an `extra=\"forbid\"` model (so *undeclared params* still 422) and validating the *date value* with an imperative `parse_daily_date` that raises `HTTPException(400)`. Flagged in Stack notes as a conscious deviation.\n2. **Metric-only grouping** (collapsing `customer_id`) — the brief gives only `date` and asks for \"per-metric\" counts. Flagged as Open Question 1.\n3. **No new index / no migration** — a covering index would add write-path index-maintenance cost to `POST /v1/events`, brushing the no-behavior-change constraint; the `api_key_id`-prefix scan is bounded + rate-limited. Deferred; Open Question 4.\n4. **Tenant scope from the principal only** (no `customer_id`/`api_key_id` input) — removes the IDOR parameter by construction.\n\n## Threat model rigor\n\nThe two brief-highlighted threats are addressed explicitly: **tenant-isolation/IDOR** (H) via `api_key_id`-first predicate + RLS backstop, with the \"no object id in the input surface\" structural argument; and **DoS/unbounded query** (M) via single-day aggregate over the pre-aggregate + `[now−90d, now+1d]` date bound + Tier-2 per-key and Tier-1 IP throttles. Every mitigation names a concrete mechanism, file, and enabling condition. The `date` validation contract gives type + anchored allowlist (`^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}$`, ReDoS-safe) + calendar check + range bound + the bound-param sink it protects; the endpoint's single input source carries both required input-surface ACs (validation = AC3–AC6, rate-limit = AC13).\n\n`audit-trail`/`regulated-data`/`data-protection` skills were evaluated and ruled **out of scope** with reasons (non-sensitive operational metering data; pure read, stores nothing). The plan documents the `mtr_live`/`Bearer` auth context so `test_dast_context_documented` continues to pass.\n\n**Self-audit:** passed — all applicable rubric items present (layer sections, inline what/why/how, STRIDE with mechanisms, validation contracts incl. undeclared-param rule, Mermaid DFD + LLM prompt, concrete Files affected, `pyramid` test strategy, Stack notes, Open questions, traceable acceptance criteria). The one gap caught and corrected during audit was a missing **## Stack notes** section, now added.\n\nPlan is ready for human review. Stopping here — I did not write application code, and a human reviews the plan + threat model next."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14076,"cache_read_input_tokens":126279,"output_tokens":2233,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":14076},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":2233,"cache_read_input_tokens":126279,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14076,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":14076,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccvuip4Zm5rR8wuP5ju8r","attributionAgent":"planning","type":"assistant","uuid":"6f986d21-94b9-48fc-8b49-a2f543504aaf","timestamp":"2026-07-11T20:35:23.617Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
